body.prompt:
Generate a fake conversation between a customer and an agent.
The agent should introduce themselves, their company and give the customer
their name. The agent should ask for the customer's name.
As part of the conversation, have the agent ask for two pieces of
personal information.  Spell out numbers. For example, 1000 should be
said as one zero zero zero, not one thousand. The conversation should be
at least 10 lines long and be complete. At the end
of the conversation, the agent should thank the customer for their time
and end the conversation. Return the conversation formatted 
like the following example:

{'conversation': 
    [
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': 'xxxxx'}, 
    {'speaker': 'Customer', 'message': "xxxxx."}, 
    {'speaker': 'Agent', 'message': "xxxxxx"}
    ] 
}

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Hello! Thank you for contacting Palm Auto. My name is Willie Martin. May I have your name, please?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Hi there! My name is Cynthia Stewart.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Nice to meet you, Cynthia! Can you please provide me with your phone number?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Sure, my phone number is five five five, three eight two, four nine six one.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Thank you, Cynthia. And could you also let me know your email address?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: Of course! My email is cynthia dot stewart at example dot com.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: Great, thank you for providing that information, Cynthia. Is there anything specific you're looking for today?

body.speaker: Customer
body.message: I'm interested in browsing your inventory of SUVs. I feel excited about finding the perfect one.

body.speaker: Agent
body.message: That's wonderful to hear, Cynthia! I'll be more than happy to assist you with that. Thank you for your time today.
